abstract: Intel posts net income of $3.5 billion, or 65 cents a share, for its third quarter, a 17 percent improvement over the same period last year, beating Wall Street forecasts; sales for the quarter rise 28 percent to $14.2 billion from $11.1 billion.
snippet: The chip company posted net income of $2.96 billion, a 17 percent improvement over the same period last year.
lead_paragraph: The chip company posted net income of $2.96 billion, a 17 percent improvement over the same period last year.
